cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) for spoken dialogue systems, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses a conditional variational autoencoder architecture, which is a type of neural network commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the diversity of generated sentences, which is a topic in statistical dialogue systems (cs.SD). Finally, the paper proposes a new model that improves performance with limited training data, which is a common problem in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE).
